  "key": "TSK-0132",
  "title": "Fix Page Search Score=0.0 Under-Ranking",
  "description": "Research Report R1-013 (Confidence 91%, High). Pages returned from MemorySmith search have Score=0.0, causing them to be systematically under-ranked compared to memory records — even when the page content is more relevant. This misleads planners and LLMs relying on search ordering.\n\nRoot Cause (confirmed by code audit 2026-06-26):\n- MemorySmith.SearchController.cs:53 — pages get `Score=null` from `UnifiedSearchResult`\n- PageSummary model (PageService.cs:216) has NO Score property at all\n- Sorting: `.OrderByDescending(result => result.Score ?? 0)` pushes pages to bottom\n- Agent side: RestMemoryGateway.SearchAsync faithfully maps null→0.0 via `h.Score ?? 0.0`\n- SearchMemoryTool ignores Score entirely — just uses first result as `bestPageId`\n\nFix approach (two-tier):\n\n**Tier 1 (Agent-side, within scope):**\n1. In RestMemoryGateway.SearchAsync (line ~46), assign a minimum score to page results:\n   - Pages: Score = max(0.05, existing score) so they aren't pushed to absolute bottom\n   - Memories: preserve original score\n2. In SearchMemoryTool, when building result dictionary, include Score per result\n3. Optionally: scan page results for coordinate patterns too (like memory results)\n\n**Tier 2 (Cross-repo — MemorySmith server):**\n1. Add Page relevance scoring to MemorySmith (lexical BM25 or semantic)\n2. `PageSummary` record needs a `double? Score` property\n3. Sort unified results with a fair interleaving algorithm instead of score-only\n\nCross-repo request should be filed under MS-Requests.\n\nFiles:\n- Agent.Memory/RestMemoryGateway.cs:34-47 (SearchAsync)\n- Agent.Tools/Tools/SearchMemoryTool.cs:48-91 (ExecuteAsync)\n- MemorySmith/MemorySmith.App/Controllers/SearchController.cs:26-61 (API)\n- MemorySmith/MemorySmith.App/Services/PageService.cs:216 (PageSummary)\n\nSource: research-MemorySmith.Agent Sprint-35 Code Audit, Council Addendum 2026-06-26. Code audit: SteveBot 2026-06-26.,
